{
  "semantic_description": "Scans a null-terminated ASCII string of length n and checks whether bracket characters (), [], and {} are properly matched using a local stack buffer of size 128. The input string is read-only and contains no embedded zero byte before the terminator. The main control structure is one while loop with early returns on unmatched closing brackets or mismatched bracket types; on normal exit it returns 1 exactly when the simulated stack is empty and 0 otherwise. The function mutates only its local stack array and preserves the caller-owned string buffer unchanged.",
